    Fix intermittent OSX CI errors (#842)

    We were seeing intermittent failures in OSX CI. This seems to be because
    the symbol address lookup was returning invalid addresses on OSX .

    We check to make sure the interpreter address is valid after getting the
    address from symbols, and if it isn't we fallback to scanning the BSS section
    for the interpreter.  On OSX, this fallback wasn't always getting triggered -
    if the _PyRuntime address pointed to valid memory we would detect that
    the it was invalid and trigger the fallback - but if it pointed to an
    invalid address in the target process we just returned an error and failed
    to load. This caused intermittent failures on CI. This fix makes it
    so that we will run the BSS ballback even if the _PyRuntime address
    points to invalid memory.

    Fixing the OSX symbol resolution so that we get valid addresses will
    happen in a separate PR.
