commit 0c6c0b54f7f6ff43577f767bfdbb2a88f510d77f
Author: Ben Frederickson <github@benfrederickson.com>
Date:   Sun Oct 20 12:15:54 2019 -0700

    Support for profiling subprocesses

    Add support for profiling subprocesses in the top and record options, via
    a ```--subprocesses``` flag. In the record option we show the process
    tree in the flamegraph, and the top view we will show the # of processes
    and the merged activity across processes.

    This refactors how we are collecting samples into a 'Sampler' class,
    where the sampling is happening on a different thread. For the subprocesess
    case we fan out to a new thread for each python subprocess, and also have
    a separate thread to monitor for new child processes every 100ms. The
    single process case will only have a single extra thread to collect samples.
    In both cases we communicate back to the main thread using a mpsc Channel.

    This also adds code to list the child processes to the remoteprocess
    crate for Linux/FreeBSD/Windows and OSX.
