Author: Ben Frederickson <github@benfrederickson.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 28 22:32:45 2018 -0700

    Support python installed via homebrew on OSX

    Python installed from homebrew on OSX has a different layout than both
    the system python and packages from python.org/anaconda.

    For instance the Python executable is something like:
    /usr/local/Cellar/python/3.6.4_2/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.6/Resources/Python.app/Contents/MacOS/Python
    And the libpython filename is: /usr/local/Cellar/python/3.6.4_2/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.6/Python

    Support this by matching the homebrew python filenames appropiately.
---
 src/python_spy.rs | 22 ++++++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

